**************
The problem requires finding \(P(Y_7 < 27.3)\), where \(Y_7\) is the seventh order statistic in a sample of eight independent observations from a continuous distribution with a 70th percentile of \(\pi_{0.7} = 27.3\).

For a continuous distribution, \(P(Y_7 < 27.3) = P(Y_7 \leq 27.3)\), and this is equivalent to the probability that at least seven of the eight observations are less than or equal to 27.3. Since \(P(X \leq 27.3) = 0.7\), where \(X\) is a single observation, this probability follows a binomial distribution with \(n = 8\) and \(p = 0.7\).

Thus, \(P(Y_7 < 27.3) = P(X \geq 7)\) where \(X \sim \text{Binomial}(8, 0.7)\). This is calculated as:
\[
P(X = 7) + P(X = 8) = \binom{8}{7} (0.7)^7 (0.3)^1 + \binom{8}{8} (0.7)^8 (0.3)^0
\]
\[
= 8 \times (0.7)^7 \times 0.3 + (0.7)^8
\]
\[
= 8 \times 0.0823543 \times 0.3 + 0.05764801
\]
\[
= 8 \times 0.02470629 + 0.05764801
\]
\[
= 0.19765032 + 0.05764801 = 0.25529833
\]

Rounding to three significant figures, the result is 0.255.

The answer has no unit, as it is a probability.

