The mean is \(\mu = p = 0.25\) and the variance is \(\sigma^2 = \frac{p(1-p)}{n} = \frac{0.25 \times 0.75}{500} = 0.000375\). With \(\epsilon = 0.05\), \(\epsilon^2 = 0.0025\), so \(\frac{\sigma^2}{\epsilon^2} = \frac{0.000375}{0.0025} = 0.15\).

