The solution calculates \( P(A) \) using the given probabilities \( P(A \cup B) = 0.76 \) and \( P(A \cup B') = 0.87 \). After applying the formulas for the union of events and simplifying the equations, the solution arrives at \( P(A) = 0.63 \). This result is verified by substituting it back into the original equations, confirming consistency.

The final answer is $0.63$.
