* N: 1 *
********
**************
* RESPONSE 1 *
**************
The solution calculates the probability of at least one match by finding the complementary probability of no matches. The probability of no matches is \( \left( \frac{11}{12} \right)^{12} \approx 0.351996 \), so the probability of at least one match is \( 1 - 0.351996 = 0.648004 \). This result is rounded to three significant figures, giving 0.648.

The final answer is $0.648$
